Combine the tags array with separate tags, sorted, including __name__:
{'__name__':'http_requests_count','env':'dev','region':'eu'}
A Map is accepted as the tags array:
{'__name__':'http_requests_count','env':'dev','region':'eu'}
Only the tags array, no separate pairs:
{'a':'1','b':'2'}
A duplicate tag name is removed:
{'job':'api'}
A tag with an empty value is dropped:
{'region':'eu'}
A NULL tag value means the tag is absent:
{'region':'eu'}
An empty separate value does not conflict with the same tag in the array (the array value wins):
{'__name__':'bar','x':'1'}
Empty input produces an empty map:
{}
